title: Can I be Yours?
author: amber l. l.
text: can i be yours to the very end? can i take me heart with yours and mend?  your love is like and inflatable balloon.  5 it keeps burgeoning,  although never bursting to soon.   you and me,  we are the same i was down when your love first came.   when i'm with you i'm as tall as an  10 everwood tree.  when you're with me,  you are like a bird trying to flee.   i can look at you all day and never get tired.  15 i'll still be admiring you if i were to be rapt in a fire.   my affection is unconditionally blind.  at last a heart i did find.   so,  can i be yours forever more? 20 if not,  my heart will become fragile and sore.   **************************************** it is me again,  i wrote the poems nobody to somebody and to the brave ones.   *going to keep writing untill it is time for me to leave from this earth!

title: Nobody to Somebody
author: amber l.l.
text: i don't know who you are,  but i'm  nobody.  if i nobody than you might be somebody.   i'm nothing,  like a dot in the crowd 5 you are hot and spicy; i am mild  you are everything and prominent.   again i am nothing and dormant.   i'm like the brown leaf on the ground.   your like the trees above- so astound.   10 i'm like a bat in a lonely cave.  your like a gladiator,  well known and brave.   i'm as small as ant.  you're the lion that roars,  but i can't!  10 you are the being awed all around.  i am the ground getting stepped on,  so down.   although,  i know who i am from the start. . .  15 iam somebody. . . somebody in my heart!                ****************   i have a profound passion for poems.  i just want someone to unerstand me and understand the way i was expressing myself in the many poems i write.  i believe that there is so much more to poetry that life can handle.  this poem was about me just being me and separating myself from the rest of the world.  on the outside i am a nobody because everyone else interpret themselves as a somebody.  i don't want to be like everyone else.  i desire to show the world i can display myself as an individual and my very own person.  again,  i just want anyone,  especially  (the people my age) to understan. . d where i'm coming from with my poetry.  i don't think about ryhming,  stanzas,  brainstorming,  prewritning,  lines,  different types of poems etc.  i think about the love of writing,  i don't even think about why i'm writing sometimes- i just write.  although,  of course i go over it when i'm done expressing myself.  then after words,  i read the poem,  i become one with it,  then i think of how poignant it is to me and only me.  i think if i stopped writing,  i would stop living and i have only just begun! in conclusion,  i want someone to understand me because when i read others poems,  i comprehend them. . .    *thankyou for taking your time reading this.

title: To the Brave Ones
author: amber l.l.
text: to my american soliders:  faith. . .  courage. . .  love. . .  hope without you,  we can't cope.   keep hope alive,  so we can survive.  to make life better you have strived.   5 you will come home. . .  you are not alone. . .    when hope was gone,  faith came in.  we love you soliders i could say it again.   10 your courage is like peace and love.  never ending,  always above.   your as high as the mightiest mountain.  we can drink hope from the mighty fountain.   15 your bravery is like the affection of a true friend.  it never stops,  never terminates,  and never ends!  our prayers are with you every step of 20 the way.  count on america,  we will never leave you stray.   god bless america. . .  god bless the world.  25 god bless every man,  woman,  boy,  and girl.   we are in this ordeal together.  we can make it through stormy weather.   soliders dry your eyes. . .  30 children no more cries. . .   we are like an active volcano,  never giving in; blasting out courage again and again.   we are americans,  we can make it! 35 this wasn't meant to be but we can take it!  soliders you are astoundingly prominent where you stand.  all the soliders in our hearts from  40 woman to man.   soldiers,  when you feel all hope is gone. . .  remember,  you are coming home!

title: Steel Bars
author: amy
text: as a young girl i watched as my father slipped silently behind steel bars.  the feeling of being chained or closed off from society filled the empty space around.   loss of a father,  a dad,  a family member filled my discomforting home.  social workers came,  played games,  asked questions i shied from; they made me feel small.   talking on phones,  seen behind glass,  i grew up independent.  loss of friendships,  not playing sports,   held me back socially.  my family took care of each other,  no matter what happened.  it was plastered  in the newspaper and everyone in town knew my tragic,  unforgiving story,  i lost hope of being a normal kid;  told myself i was crazy for the things that occurred  throughout my childhood.  therapists,  guidance counselors,  discussed my situation with me.  tears dripped down my face as i  wrote letters and saw family pictures.  september,  before labor day,  my father came home.   eight years old before my birthday,  a smile from ear to ear,  i dug my head into his chest.  different,  thatâ’s how i felt.  everything changed;  some things became better,  others not so much.   i had grown up,  my dad noticed.  we created stories and shared old ones.  i was so excited  to have my dad back,  or thatâ’s what i thought.   we became a family and my repeated christmas wish finally came true.  that year was different.  memories were made,  good and bad ones,  but iâ’ll never forget  the day i lost my dad to those steel bars.

title: The Swing
author: andy
text: the sun beams down,  blazing its heat on the crowd.  green grass stays settled and calm,  for there is no wind.  the players standing on the crimson dirt let sweat roll lazily off their face.   a tall skinny man wearing long socks,  a baggy pair of pants,  and a shirt a size to big,  standing firmly on the mound that makes him raise above everyone else.  his hat's brim shades his face from the light of the sun.   his blue eyes stare down the batter standing beside home plate.  he grips his bat tight,  knowing he is about to get a fastball.  the pitcher rocks back and raises his leg up to this chest.   with his arm cocked back he whizzes in a blazing pitch.  the hitter stays calm,  waiting for the perfect time to swing.  crack.  the little white ball goes flying of the pine bat like a rocket into space.  the pitcher turns his head and watches the ball float a mile into the sky.  three outfielders begin running towards the ball,  following the flight of the ball.  sadly they have to stop as the ball flies over the big black wall.  with all the ease the batter drops his batting and begins his victory trot.

title: An Equine Frendship
author: anna
text: i glanced at the meadow,  and instantly spot,  a young,  wild-hearted horse,  still confused by being caught.   as i stared at the mare,  i knew she was for me.  the painted horse galloped,  as her hooves beat the ground,  her eyes filled with glee.   she pricked her ears,  pointed directly to the sun,  then,  she cantered around in a circle.  i noticed she was having fun.   her walk was mellow,  her trot was proud.  her canter was smooth,  then i saw her move to a gallop as her hoof beats became loud.   she hovered the ground,  in her every stride.  then she slowed to a trot,  she trotted with pride.  then she walked towards me,  and i looked into her eyes,  which was all beautiful,  majestic,  and kind.   her coat was like a milky white canvas,  splashed with crimson like paint.  her eyes flickered in the sunlight  i just couldn't stand it,  so i did what i thought was right.   i ran to the stable and got a saddle,  bridle,  and girth.  and dreamed that it would work,  dreamed that they would be galloping across the earth.  so i put the tack on her,  she didn't seem to mind.  i held my breath and jumped on her.  first,  a walk,  trot,  canter,   and we galloped as the sun shined.   i realized she moved rather gawkily.  so i unmounted and patted her thigh.  as she stomped her hoof,  snorted and sighed.  then i realized what she wanted me to do.  i lifted the saddle off her back and rested it beside,  then,  removed her silver bridle,  and hoped for the best,  as i jumped on her back,  and let her do the rest.   she trotted so freely and carelessly that i let her choose what she wanted to do,  so she moved onto a smooth canter.  i felt so free and happy,   and that's when i knew,  a friendship was brewing,  faithfully anew.

title: You're An Angel

title: The Keepers
author: arianna
text: lies are golden,  smothered in rich.  eaten with pleasure,  swallowed quick.   disguises the truth,  with it's white lies.  under the skin,  the lies hide.   buried within,  forgotten among.  growing inside us,  leaving the scars.   untold secrets within,  covered in chains,  hidden in dark.  growing inside us,  leaving the marks.   stomachs churn,  and eyes close.  forgetting the wrong,  burying them deeper,  locking them away,  they are the keepers.

title: Sorry
author: ariel
text: sorry i wasn't there,  i didn't even know,  it was your special day,  i should've known.   i must be the worst friend alive,  i am so sorry! i feel so bad down inside,  i felt so bad,  i cried! you mean so much to me,  we've always been best friends,  i'm so sorry i wasn't there for you today,  the day you turned into a woman.

title: I Should've Known
author: ariel
text: so close,  let down my walls,  never made a sound,  never faced my fear.   fear takes over,  lights stay on,  i lay awake hearing every sound.   when it's gone,  a deep exhale,  except when the news came,  fear conquered again.

title: HEARTS
author: ariel
text: when someone is lost,  it breaks hearts.  hearts of many,  people who knew the loved one,  people who had no clue,  people who never got to say that final goodbye,  people who disliked them,  too.   so many hearts were broken yesterday and today,  they gathered as one,  brought flowers and prayed,  that loved one will never know,  will never know how much people loved them,  may they still live on,  and go back to school in spirit to comfort the grieving hearts monday.

title: Just Friend
author: ariel
text: as i pass through the crowd,  only one thing dawns on me,  i'm alone,  where's my friends,  my family?  no where to be seen,  i'm all alone,  i turn a corner,  and there they are! a frown crosses my face.   these friends,  they are not my friends,  they never have been,  the only way i can tell is because they don't miss me.   my friends have moved on,  what was i? a worthless person in the world? they extaticly talk,  shouldn't they be unhappy? i mean,  i must have meant something to them!  then i see it,  i meant my friends just friend.

title: Rumours
author: ariel
text: shifty eyes,  guarded glances,  whispers exchanged,  laughing kids with mean faces.   is there something going on i should know about? more laughter errupts throught my day,  nasty looks of pity,  what happened? did i do something wrong?  one girl comes up to me,  one of the populars,  you see,  she tells me i shouldn't be wearing that shirt,   with those stockings and short skirt.   i thank her quietly for her advice,  and silently cry,  for who is she to tell me what i can wear? i should be the only person to care.

title: Games
author: ariel
text: i see the choices you make,  the people who you hang out with,  the type of stuff they tell you to do,  and you're the one to follow them.   i know you're smarter than that,  i know you can do better,  the people you hang out with,  don't care about other's feelings.   i have feelings too,  and this is what i know,  that stupid game called zap,  is hurting everyone i know.   it's telling them your worthless,  just a random person who someone would stick gum in their hair,  by playing the game that you play,  you're saying they're not there,  invisible as a plane behind the clouds that no one could ever care about.   i know it's just for fun,  and friends can get you carried away,  but please have enough sense,   to hear what i'm about to say,  it lowers self-esteem that many do not have,  and make them feel the world's come to an end because they are non-existant.

title: Don't  You  Know?
author: ariel
text: if you look around,  do you notice anything different? i mean,  look closer,  that one tiny little thing you saw yesterday may not be the same today,  is it one of your friends? maybe.   do people notice they change every day? whether it be clothing they wear,  or the friends they choose,  people continue to change,  even you.   what am i doing here? who are you? this world is forever changing,  our friendship ends and continues to grow,  too.   not anymore,  this constant game we play,  act normal.  step up to the plate! i know you can,  don't let those other people have influence over you,  you have a mind,  use it,  too.   we were friends,  then not,  we're friends again,  so what's up? i may understand they're still your friends,  but don't forget all the goodtimes we once had.   sure we were young,  you may not remember clearly,  neither i,  but we can still always be friends.

title: People
author: ariel
text: people say that time flies by,  well,  they're right.  something that's happened in the summer,  is now the past,  now in february.  if you go to the city,  traffic moves fast.  people are in a rush,   and you get caught up in the moment.  you seem to say to yourself,  what's the hurry? if you have all the time in the world,  why waste it in a hurry? savour every moment,  whether a birthday,  or a snow day.

title: Winter Skies
author: ariel
text: you'd think someone would forget the worst,  and remember the best,  past,  present,  what's the difference?   it happened then,  bothers me still now,  what difference does it really make,  season,  year,  or month.   my feelings will remain the same,  words gone unsaid,  they can't be repeated now,  except in the head.   the closest people know,  some have yet to know,  until that time,  expressing  myself is what i know.

title: Without You
author: ariel
text: without you,  i am blue,  without you,  the sun doesn't shine,  without you by my side sometimes,  the  rain comes pouring down,  without you,  i bare a frown,  when you're gone,  it's not the same,  even when surrounded by others,  it's not the same feeling that i get,  when i'm around you.   without you,  i would be lonely,  without you,  i would cry day in and day out,  without you in my life,  i would never be the person that i am today,  so i wrote this little poem to say,  i love you as a friend,  and i never want you to go away,  and to show you how much you mean to me.

title: Words Hurt
author: ash;ey
text: you should know,  bullying hurts.  it starts with one word,  one word you blurt.  fat,  ugly,  worthless.  these are the words they hear.  did you know your their biggest fear?  day by day you torment them,  it takes so long for their hearts to mend.  all they ask for is one true friend,  but you make them want their lives to end.   everyday they wake up with regret,  all they want to do is forget.  its not just hitting and punching,  its the words you say,  they hurt so much,  they want to fade away.   this is when enough is enough,  they`re sick of playing strong,  sick of playing tough.  but they know they can make it through,  you may not have known but they always knew.   they put on a fake smile and pretend they`re okay,  they believe they can make it all the way.  of course your words still offend,  but they have pieced back together again.   someone leaves the crowd and lends them a hand,  they learn that its time to stand.  their smile is no longer fake,   now they have no reason to ache.   you see,  all they ever needed was a friend,  someone to stand by them when the bullying came again.  now they are free,  the insults barely sting,  don't you see?  the bully is never wanted,  unless wanted to leave,  the person you bullied now has no need for long sleeves.  your work here is done,  not that it should've started,  now who`s the one who feels broken hearted?  bullying gave you power,  that they refused to give,  you cant help but wonder ''what if''.  what if they didn't get so strong? what if they were crumbled all along?  what you don't think of,  is what could've been,  what if they pulled the razor to their skin? what if you pushed them too far,  to where they tied a rope around their collar.   what if they wrote down all the secrets they had to spill,  right before taking an overdose on the pills? you don't know what could've been done,  you were doing it all for fun.   you think they`re losers,  but they`re stronger than you,  have you seen what they've been through? with your words you gave a black eye,  they are leaving,  bully,  so say your goodbye.   but one more thing before you go,  did you enjoy my little show? remember,  words can hurt more than the punch,  believe me now? cause this was just a hunch.

title: My mom means more to me
author: ashley
text: my mom means more to me than the sun rising and the moon setting,  it's like i can't live without her,  she's there for me through thick and thin,  i see her in the stars,  i can hear her whispers in the sky,   i hear her voice through the wind,  i can her laughs in the sun,  i can see her face in the moon,  i see nothing but memories with her,  ican see the future in the lights,  it's like an hourglass planning the next day,  we're like planets so close together,  we always have a story to tell,  it's like a big story chest full of memories,   we always have a shoulder to cry on,  we always have a tear to grab,  our tears are like ice cycles waiting to drop,  we always have the galaxy to fill,  we never know when we're down, we're always lifted to the clouds,  we float on top,  our world is like a diamond,  always shiny and easy to read,  but when were gone,  we won't be alone,  my mom means more to me

title: Unwelcome Visitors
author: ashley
text: when i awoke one morning,  a mouse snoozed on my head.  i asked ''what are you doing there?'' it looked at me and said,  ''i am so very tired,  and i'm in desperate need of sleep.  i was thrown out of my house,  and into a trash heap. ''  ''oh my,  i am so sorry, '' i said with deep sorrow.  ''you can stay here today,  and stay as well tommorow. '' ''thank you so much kind sir,  you've helped me meet loose ends.  i do have one request though: i brought a couple friends. ''  he pointed to the left.  i looked in his direction.  i stared in great surprise,  he stared in great affection.  in came a million mice,  furry and lost and small.  they crawled across the floor,  and skittered up the wall.   my house has changed alot,  it will never be the same.  the mice are all my friends,  i gave them each a name.  sometimes i wish they'd leave,  but i have to pay the price.  when you live in a house of cheese,  you must expect mice.

text: the flower was very big,  next to it was a great big twig.  the flower once like a little baby,  now appears like a beautiful lady.   it lived in a garden under a tree,  it was very hard to see.  then one day she got picked,  by a boy who they called rick.   she got put in a jar,  from her home she was very far.  in the jar she felt surrounded,  she liked it better when she was grounded.   then she felt very sick,  for it was her that he did pick.  if he would just had inspected her,  she would still be alive for sure.

title: A beautiful day
author: ayushi
text: the sun shines bright in the clear skies,  the breeze is cold and soft,  the sweet smell of flowers,  the song of birds above,   the beautiful morning is here.   the rustling falls,   the sun is strong,   the heat of the afternoon  melts the snow .  .  .  .   the ball of fire is now  at the edge,  the colour of skies,  turns orange and blue,   and after some time,   the ball of fire,  extinguishes,   hiding behind the mountain.   the moonlit sky,  the twinkling stars,   tell us the time,  to sleep,  is here.

title: The Motherly Face
author: ayushi
text: on a very fine day,   when i came to school,  i saw a motherly face,  wearing a sweet smile; and the slightest bit  of nervousness,  the tiniest shadow of fear,  was out of my mind at once and for all; the cheerful clouds were here.   and from that day,  this  motherly face,  has given me hope in times of sorrow,   love and help whenever i need.   do you want to know,  who is this motherly face? maybe you're surprised,   but teacher,  it's you!

title: Parents' Day
author: ayushi
text: the first time i opened my eyes into this world,  i saw the ones who brought me,  into this world.   the care you took,  the smiles you shared,  the love you gave,  will always be there in my heart,  forever and forever. . . .   i wish this day,  i could give you,  a jar of moonbeams,  or a rainbow,  and all the good things in this world.   but till i learn how to catch rainbows or moonbeams,  i'd like to say a very special,    ' happy parents' day! ' from the bottom of my heart. . . .

title: I Am Me

title: What's In The Heart

text: love is what we were born with like a glossy river was born with a natural flow you donâ’t know where or how itâ’ll take you all you know is it relaxes you,  it calms you  believe in yourself,  donâ’t  give up before you rush to start when your heart starts to yell out ,  drum drum,  like a snare  itâ’s trying to tell you something,  something,  something,  something thatâ’s not even there to begin with  fear is in your heart as much as love,  donâ’t know if itâ’s true they equally share a home down there in the waxy,  warm,  structure both take over,  just like a queen bee and her hive never to reveal themselves,  only to make us learn ourselves  love may seem stronger at times,  when it starts to race when your thoughts start going,  at any random place when all your heart can do is smile largely a lot and itâ’s emotions swimming quite wildly  fear may also seem stronger at times,  when you start to shake when your heart makes your chest really ache or when you walk with your head bent down low or when you feel the only cure is to breakdown and cry  truth is,  neither is stronger than the other,  nor more powerful their power together is what is dominating it love and fear merge together like two colors do to make one whole and that is what they do,  the come together to create the heart

title: Lost
author: becca
text: i wake up one morning,  don't know where i am.  everything is dark,  the ground is cold.  i'm not wearing anything,  i'm naked to the eye.  i'm freezing and don't know what to do,  i curl up in a ball to keep any warmth there is,  inside.  looking everywhere,  i can see that no one is around,  i want to go home with my family and friends,  i need someone to be with me.  the ground is now warm,  my body is hot.  i realize now,  that this is god's way,  it is god's way of teaching me,  that everyone needs someone,  to keep them company.  as i think,  the light comes back.  i'm in my room,  on my bed,  my clothes are on again.  now,  i will never forget,  the night that i was lost in my room.

title: Truth Roses
author: becca
text: sunlit petals of roses appear to be perfect in a gentle way but the truth behind their loveliness can be shown through  a normal day the inside of its flower has a powdery yellow pollen bowl and is some times empty and sometimes full roses can give certain people the sniffles,  because of allergies  and brighten a couples day on their anniversary they symbolize love and give one the strength to share emotions while their silky petals are as smooth as the most gentle lotions  their colors jump out at the running eyes of the admirer  and possesses the knowledge of what you wish it to express by imagining a rose as a person in a stance  you can relate the two in a simple glance roses can prickle,  stab,  and sting but perform wonders and be a mending wing  as roses arenâ’t perfect,  for nothing is everyone can relate--.

title: A Way Of Life

text: one day i awoke and saw something broke so i went outside to see what it was and come to find out it was a dove  the poor little dove all-helpless in love was little to say that it was not in my way.  i bent over and picked up the poor little dove to see that it was in shock because it has just a block.  the poor little dove all helpless and lost i took it inside to take care of and to teach it to fly.    a few days later i came to my room and notice the bird was awake and sitting on top of my wonderful candle.  i say to the bird i see you are better now it is time to teach you to fly.  the little bird notice that the window was opened and ran to the floor and the bed.  i saw that the bird was hiding to stay in my room because it did not want to leave.  it did not want me to teach it to fly so i called up the vet to see what was the matter with this little turtledove.  the nice little vet told me that the dove did not want to leave because it was in love with me.  so i told the vet goodbye and looked at the dove and said we have got to fly.    the next i am outside trying to get the bird to fly but it is not working so well.  so then i look away for a few minutes and then all of a sudden it started to fly but to my next-door neighbor and landed apon his head.  i run over to get the little dove and to see for my eyes this wonderful guy.  we talked and ate for hours on end and by the end of the night i had found my special love all from a dove that i found caught in a glove.

title: As the Earth Turns
author: bibi
text: i sit on the sandy shore watching the range of vision,  5 more minutes till it disappears 5 minutes is what i have left  on the shore  orange,  yellow,  and red the wavy blue,  transparent,  odorless water the range of vision disappearing in the ocean slowly and softly  no splashes to be seen darker and darker it gets darkened,  as the lighthouse that turns upon the sea.   the only light left is the light of my eyes  as i walk along the shore  i see that the range of vision has gone before my eyes i walk down to the south of the shore i touch the still water for the last time  my feet feel the coldness of the water it wrinkles my toes the longer i stand in it the shells glide along my legs and the sand in between my toes  i step out of the water and walk towards my house i turn around to look at the water one last time but nothing is left i turn back round and walk in the door and close it the next thing i see is the darkness of my eyes

title: A Young Golfer...
author: brandon
text: the day had just begun,  it was dim and damp,   everyone was around to see a true champ.   he couldnâ’t judge the slope,  and couldnâ’t decide  which way each putt broke.   as he approached the par three tee-box the grass soft and fuzzy,  he looked down the fairway and felt a little dizzy.   there was a bunker on the left,  and a bunker on the right.  the green was almost challenging him,  saying to him,   youâ’ll need a little spin.   he pulled out his five wood from his bag,  while everyone was still and watching.  he teed his golf ball up,  while tugging on his hat.   he took two smooth practice swings,  and on his third shot,   struck the ball perfectly solid.  it was right on target to the hole,  it was just like a bullet.   as he walked up to see where his ball was  he did not see it in sight.  he walked up to the hole  to see if it had gone in,  and held his face with fright.   and sure enough,  there his ball lay in the hole,  facing up to him.  he bent down to pick up the ball,  which put a grin on his chin.   as he held his ball up with pride and joy.  he went over to hug his father,  for this moment,  was a moment that would always last forever.

title: THE GREEN MONSTER
author: brisa and sarah
text: his footsteps creak on floorboards that are weak,  he is covered in ugly gore,  the king of impending doom emerges from his room,  exploding with a gruesome roar.      a malicious monster with grumbling groans and sickly dark green skin,  two outstretched hands with cuts and gashes,  and eyes that shine like tin.    a loose screw,  two torn tennis shoes and clumps of greasy black hair,  worn and worked and weathered pants that frame an ugly tear.    he lumbers past,  not moving fast,  and blasts a horrible scream.  as he limps past,  as if in a cast,  he tries to haunt your dreams.    take care to hide when he stumbles by to give your dreams a spell,  what he may do with a dream or two can cause someone to yell.

title: The new and the old.
author: brittany
text: my phone is the most important thing to me,    i use it all the time.    you cannot see the ware and tear of this use,    for it is brand new.    the deep blue and black is shiny,    and very smooth.      on the back is a piece of tape,    giving the image that it is broken,    but it's not,    it's just different than yours.      a tanish cup that's very big,    with 3d outlines of many people.    ohio state football players   running to score a touchdown.    people in the stands,    cheering and screaming.      my phone is a lot of what i know,    the cup is brand new to me.    my phone was just made last week,    the cup has been here for years.      life after life and death after death,    everything is new or old.

title: Teenage Years
author: brittany
text: when a little kid is playing in the yard,  and an adult drives by,  they stop to wish that they were them.   everyone wants to grow up,  everyone wants to become an adult.  to drive and spend money and do whatever they want.  but what they donâ’t know,   is that you have to earn that money.  and buy that car and gas.  and put your responsibilities before fun.   when an adult is behind on bills,  and foreclosure is threatening their home,  they wish to be young again.   everyone wants to take a break,  everyone wants to just have some fun.  to just play all day and sleep,  and your only worries are losing a ball,  or failing a test.  but what they donâ’t remember,  is that they once wished to be older,  as they are now wishing to be younger.   everyone wants to be old,  everyone wants to be young,  but some just want to be in the middle,  a teenager for good.

title: Waiting
author: brittany
text: i sit in my room alone waiting,  waiting for some one to here me.  here me yell,  here me scream.   i lay alone in my living room waiting,  waiting for somebody to feel me.  feel me cry,  feel me laugh.   i stand against a wall alone waiting,  waiting for one person to see me.  see me cringe,  see me tighten.   i jump rope in the gym alone waiting,  waiting for some one to smell me.  smell me fear,  smell me near.   i am alone on a building waiting,  waiting for some one to catch me.  some one like you,  some one like god.

title: To Mattie
author: brittany
text: i once knew a poetry writer,  who had muscular dystrophy.  he could move his hands and arms,   but he could not walk.   i would've never met him,  if i didn't go to john hanson m. s.  i remember everyone buying his books,  he signed them,  but i got only a hand shake.   now i go to thomas eaton m. s,   and still look for his books.  i don't hear much about him here,   and he never visits,  i  guess it's only maryland schools.   i went to maryland to visist my friend,  she told me he passed away.  so now,  i dedicate this poem to him,  from a poet to a poet.

title: Forged Intellect
author: brittany
text: what's another lie to another face? always seems the same- crowded in this empty space.   one lonely tear bleeds down my cheek,  can you not see me?  don't hold your last breath on what is and is not real.  do you think i'm emotionless? i have nothing else to feel?  look at your reflection- in the shards of broken glass.  is there even a figure? have you gone at last?  save me from my nightmare,  my disemembered dream.  or could it be my reality? my unfinished theme?

title: Moo Cow Moo
author: brooke
text: he is white with blotches of black,  always grazing the fields for a snack.  his big,  round,  bubbily eyes,   are the color of the bright blue sky.   he has a little,  fat belly,   and breath that is smelly,   and two horns on top of his head,  that are the color of whole grain bread.   he stumbles around on his short,  husky legs,   as if he is walking on a bowl of eggs.  and once in a while he'll make a sound,   that will somehow shake the whole ground.

title: Day on the River
author: brooke
text: cruising down a river as slick as glass,  after that ole allusive black bass  only eight hours to make them mine,   hope i can catch as least one nine  i'll be casting under every stump looking for just that one faint thump  i got my ole frog hopping from pad to pad,  this here fishing isn't half bad  oh,  hooked up one taking out the drag  sure hope this one's big enough for the bag  holy cow he's got my line just a singing lord if you only knew what i was thinking  oh,  please hurry and get the net dang there he goes again,  he's not ready to come just yet!  oh,  wow,  look at him jump there he goes headed for that stump  there he goes he broke my line it happened again this one won't be mine  a thousand more cast and not a bite  i guess i'll sleep good tonight   days at end,  beats in the rack these ole bass know i'll be back   well,  it weren't a bad day of fishing i guess i'll have to just keep on wishing

title: Its sometimes good to be wild.
author: brue
text: life is unexplainable but alive    wildness is a state in life    it depends on what type of person     you are    wildness sometimes brings joy,     wildness sometimes bears sorrow.            it is sometimes good to be wild    when the ups become downs    and when sorrow dwells within    when we fight against evil     wildness needs to be there.        people who are wild enjoy life to     the full of it.     wildness brings reality,  confidence    and self-confidence.     when you are wild you live according    to your own rules.       wildness is not an imagination    it is simply an action    an act of frankness    an act of reality    an act of childhood.           to me wildness is  a habit    to me wildness is my second nature    to me wildness is a gift     to me wildness is a hero    to me wildness is  a lifestyle.        that is my opinion of wildness    i am comfortable,  humble and real    in the wildest states of life    wildness is fun and i love to be wild    but the real question is    what do you think wildness truly is?

text: when i awoke one morning,   a sparrow was on my head.   i asked,  ''what are you doing there?''  it looked at me and said .  .  .     ''i flew to the north,  i flew to the west,  i flew to the east,  and here i am in the south-attop your head. '' i was confused and asked, ''but why my head,  why not a branch?'' the sparrow got nervous and barked, ''i can not go no where-for that fat cat is always somewhere!'' i was so irritated that he was my head so i thought quikly as i said,  ''why dont you let me catch that fat cat and take to the pound or maybe underground?'' he tweeted and flirted attop my head. he smiled at me,  so pleased with my idees.  i swiftly got dressed as i asked where to find that fat cat.  he said next to a tree,  towards i-90,  west bound.   so i traveled for long time,  to run along a line.  i found no fat cat-but a skinny cat who saw me and told me his plea.  i felt so sorry for the poor thing.  i said, ''i take you home to my place-i have a bird,  and hes so annoying. '' the fat cat did a quick think,  and winked at me for he was pleased.   on the way back the cat was starting to act. . .  he asked me questions about the bird-if it could fly,  if it could screech.  i was going to answer when a big great dane jumped from behind the bushes.  he growled and bickered at that fat cat.  some how he knew him. . and was not happy. i tried to devend that fat cat- i was wrong in doing so. . .   the dane ate that fat cat and bit me in reply,  and later did i find,  that he could fly.  the sparrow was attop my head again! and laughed a laugh so loud and ferocious that it sounded like a waterfall.  ''you are stuck with me again. . . ''he wispered.   now i am stuck with this bird muttated dane for the rest of my life for he does not strife.  and would you have known that his name is daneow?

title: Why
author: cecellia
text: why did you have to leave me? why did you have to go far away from where i stay,  and leave me with no hope?  you showed love and compassion.  you treated me as i were your own.  you taught me how to tie my shoes.  you taught me how to be bold.   physically you were my grandpa,  but spiritually you were my father.  you took me here,  there,  and everywhere.  now,  because of you i'm wiser.   why leave me with no words? no thought of coming back,  just to see your heavenly father.  did you even know how i'd react?  all i saw from family were tears.  all gathered in my home,  because they just found out,  that the suffering ended  but you were gone.   i didn't even cry.  i coudn't even speak.  the hurt was to much to bear' to know you went to sleep.   they told me i'll see you soon,  in glory up above.  i may have only been seven,  but  i knew these were only words of love.   it'll be a while 'till i see you; that father's face of mine.  but i may have not been who i am today unless you left me behind.                 but why?

title: My Name
author: charlie
text: my name,              my name is the seven letters that make up who i am,  they are the letters that define me.  charlie is the cracks in the floorboard that makes when you walk up the stairs.  itâ’s the sound of the laughter amplified by the movement of the trees like those dancing inflatables in front of car dealerships.  charlie means man,  warrior,  and army,  but i never feel those things.  those words are translated into a language only i can understand,  the language like the warrior iâ’m supposed to be.  charles is too formal; it is a tailored suit,  but it doesnâ’t fit me.  charlie is comfort like wind through the trees.  my name is the bunny that loses its mother,  looking into the unknown.  the keys of the piano without any strings.  it screams but no one can hear it.              my name is the remembrance of my dead grandpa,  the one who called all us chuck,  until they named me that.  itâ’s the name that makes me sad i never got to meet him but one day i will.  we share a name,  the name that tastes like the sour sweet sap that comes out of a tree.  my name is whole,  my name is complete.  i see the sadness about the remanentes of my lost twin,  the one they say that looks like me yet i canâ’t remember.  c-h-a-r-l-e-s,  charles they say,  youâ’re just like him,  but i donâ’t remember.

title: Slowly
author: chelsea
text: slowly,  comes the fall.  slowly,  walking down the hall.  slowly,  youâ’ve stopped saying â‘hiâ’.  slowly,  time passes.  slowly,  change classes.  slowly,  youâ’ve forgotten that i am alive.   slowly we depart,  as you say your silent good-bye.  and i struggle to restrain my heart,  as i try not to cry,  as you leave me behind.   slowly,  it rains.  slowly,  drops leave stains.  slowly,  iâ’ve given up trying to deny.  slowly,  it thunders.  slowly,  lightning bolts spur.  slowly,  i feel as though i could die.   slowly i shed tears,  as i try to erase you from my memory.  but youâ’ve unknowingly cast your spell and iâ’m trying to find a remedy.  yet i still want you,  as bad as youâ’ve hurt me.   slowly,  the sun sets.  slowly,  its bedtime for the rosettes.  slowly,  i close my eyes.  slowly,  the night grows darker,  as the faint stars flicker.  slowly,  you,  imposingly,  come back to mind.   you are there,  i see you; kind eyes,  warm smile,  and colored hair.  i look into your face,  we share a long,  pleasant stare.  next you smile at me.  and i hug you,  then your body disappears,   you vanish in the air and leave me in tears.   at once,  i break in painful,  sorrowful heartache.  iâ’m already in enough misery and brokeness; wonâ’t you leave me alone,  for loveâ’s sake? i wish from this nightmare i can awake.   slowly,  the night becomes a pitch black.  slowly,  the stars hit the sack.  slowly,  i toss and turn in bed.  slowly,  the night becomes silent as the grave.  slowly,  everything begins to fade.  slowly,  all this bewilderment takes over my head.   i canâ’t take this torment any longer.  iâ’m always thinking about you and it makes me so distressed and sick.  iâ’m losing my mind and all that is me,  so would be as so kind to leave?!  slowly,  the sun begins to rise.  slowly,  itâ’s bedtime for the fireflies.  slowly,  my mind begins to clear.   slowly,  darkness is broken.  slowly,  nature awakens.  slowly,  iâ’m getting away from here.   slowly,  i pick up the pieces of my shattered heart.  glue them together,  and make a beautiful art.  then i can move on,  and start my new journey head-on.   slowly,  but surely,  iâ’ve said my silent good-bye and left you behind.

title: The person within
author: chelsea
text: she runs to the mirror,  and looks at her face,   she thinks that itâ’s ugly,  thinks itâ’s a disgrace,  others must think that iâ’m disgusting and fat,  even if they didnâ’t,  sheâ’d still think that,  she tears at the mirror,  rips it off the wall,   hoping that sheâ’ll never have to look at it at all.  she collapses in bed,  and breaks down and cries,  rubbing the water away from her eyes,   she remembered the model,  the one in the book,  the way that she smiled,  the way that she looked,  her skin shade was perfect.  her stomach was thin,  she forgot what was important,  the person within,  she stopped giving her self-pity,   and hung the piece of glass back on its hook,  she stepped back in front of it,  and took a second look.   she looked beyond her reflection,  and deep down in her heart,  she had let herself be stupid,  and let herself be torn apart,  she realized she was beautiful,  on the inside and the out,   many years were wasted on self- pity,  and self- doubt,   there is something more,  past a personâ’s appearance and their skin,  causeâ’ the thing that really matters,  is the one who lies within.

title: If my eyes could take pictures

text: if my eyes could take pictures,  so perfect,   i'd take more than just photos,   but the happiest of memories.   i'd take pictures of the warm rising sun,  and the colorful sunset,  and sunwarmed fruit plucked from the dew,   and light beaming through the branches of the tall sycamore trees.   i'd take pictures of the things i love most,  of the people i love most,  even the things i hate most,   make the best of pictures.   if my eyes could take pictures,  i'd take a bike ride to the end of the world,  seeing the beautiful things this world has to give,  keeping them as memories for endless eternities.   if my eyes could take pictures,  i know that i'd dominate this earth,  and somehow,  i know,  that if my eyes could take pictures,  i could change the world.

title: Prometheus
author: chris
text: the flame.  a symbol of hope,  a symbol of knowledge.  in its glory,  it blazes like the sun.  even the greatest darkness could not diminish its light.  it is pure.  yet without darkness,  there is no light.  for we are not human without sin.  but light refreshes us,  we are pure yet again.  until darkness arises,  bringing greed with our lives.  fire.  the bringer of hope and love,  giving knowledge to us all.  we were but clumsy,  foul,  messy,  dumb animals.  our yellow rotting teeth and our big tough bodies.  we scavenge for food,  and wear skins tufted with fur.  warmth.  our only hope for a chance at survival.  without warmth we cold blooded,  ugly creatures.  frizzled,  untidy hair,  sweaty,  reeking bodies.  when light and warmth are given,  we are reborn.  light gives hope,  light gives knowledge.  with light we can see.  with sight we can learn.  with knowledge,  we can create.  and with creation,  we are powerful.  yet with power comes abuse,  and greed.  there is always a counterbalance.  light with dark.  those above us gave us this knowledge.  yet they see darkness in us.  it runs in our veins,  the black smoke,  curling through our blood.  we are canny,  but we are dumb.  we have all this power,  yet we make the silliest mistakes.  white,  glorious marble pillars,  leading to greatness.  golden statues,  sparkling in the sun.  soft,  fragile skin,  blessed with hope,  and cursed with greed.  our warm,  lively bodies.  so mysterious and elegant.  we are strong and bright.  but when we see a speck of darkness,  it grows,  deep within our hearts.  it cannot stop.  until light comes again,  we are punished eternally with the profanity of evil.  then we are not mankind anymore.  we are simply dull,  dark creatures again.  until light comes again,  until light comes again.

title: Black & white
author: christina
text: brothers,  sisters,  everywhere,  life has shunned me,  and left me bare.  dishonored,  disgraceful,  living hell,  razor sharp words,  upon i feel.  misery,  melancholy,  mixed emotions,  hungry for blood,  total annihilation.  embarrassment,  humiliation,  favors undone,  pleasure is a token,  image of fun.  doubts,  unforgiving,  in my mind,  sins of hatred left me blind.  the past,  a future,  suicidal present,  a foolish destination twisted and bent.  love,  justice,  costly consent,  my heart to you,  was it meant? desired,  tears,  i was torn,  two halves i broke,  and freedom was born.  beginning,  end,  what is life? fate unleashed,  with a knife.  darkness,  heartless,  agony of cries,  death is a sentence.  cherish lives.  the sun,  the moon,  the shining stars,  like a fantasy,  not behind bars.  eyes,  lips,  flowing hair,  my aching heart,  presents no fear.  my life,  my body,  my unique soul,  love was fulfilled,  as a transformed whole.

title: What is real

title: The Edmund Fitzgerald
author: clara
text: listen really close and you shall hear the movement of the waves   and the people in fear on november 10th,  1975 none of the 29 sailors were left alive .  the loved ones lost that were held so dear faded into darkness with only their captain near.   it all started june 7th,  1958 all the sailors and captain were off to meet their fate.  for 17 years the ship and sailors stood at their plate  up until that one treacherous date.  the edmund fitzgerald was carrying iron ore and bringing it from duluth and minnesota to detroit,  toledo,  and more.  who ever thought there would be a big storm  but the sailors went on without any warn.   ernest m.  mcsorley was the name of that man  who held that ship in powerful command.  the day before the storm they had a visitor  arthur m.  anderson was practically the ships sister.   the day of the storm arthur held close the waves were 35 feet high and so they rose.  there's no turning back â’â’we are holding our ownâ’â’ all the men knew the ship was about to drown.  the arthur and fitzgerald had lost all connection  due to the storm there was really bad reception.   there was too much water the ship was not strong before you knew it the edmund fitzgerald would be long gone.  the men said their prayers and said their goodbyes  while still fighting tears filled their eyes.  they knew they were goners they knew they were dead.  if to look up water would crash on their head.   the boat could not take the weather any more.  clear weather and one more hour the boat would be at shore.   but the time was not given,  the weather wasnâ’t right  all the men were gone on that fateful night   lake superior is where the boat is heald  and the heart of the boat is up on a shelf.   no men were found,  they were all gone  but the remembrance of the edmund fitzgerald will never be done.

title: The End
author: connor
text: i remember the end  i remember when the sky turned black.  and the oceans turned gray.  all the people perished,  on that dreadful day.  i was there when man exceeded their limits,  and thought they had won.  believed they had triumphed,  their troubles were over,  but they had just begun.  when it all began with the rain,  the heavy chemical rain,  screaming and chaos,  man was in pain.  dogs ran rabid,  barking down the street,  running in vain for their freedom.  only to be melted and succumb to the heavy acidic rain.  heavy bodies of water,  moving across land,  leaving a slug like trail of chaos and death in  their wake.  mighty warriors of the sky riding their jet black cloud steeds,  striking with lightning spears,  leaving destruction,  death and fire,  then it all stopped.  they thought it was over,  but it had only begun,  but natureâ’s revenge was over,  this time the threat was within,  now man would give over to their desire to sin.   i remember when prospects turned black.  when facing the end even the most deadest and noble of men,  on their beliefs will turn their backs.  when you know whatâ’s coming its hard to have faith,  fear mixed with greed and lust take over.  people running in chaos anarchy reigned.  rule went from one to another,  but no one was able last,  for the greed of mans true nature always took over.  survival of the fittest was law,  and that is when it was over thatâ’s how it happened,  man did not fall to war or disease,  but his own true nature,  his greed is what ended humanity,  and that was the end.

title: Missing you on Valentine's Day

text:
valentines day and im over here, thinking of your face, wishing you were near, to take me from this place.
\ni miss the feel of your lips on mine, kissing me ever so sweet, baby your always on my mind, i feel you in every heartbeat. the feel when you hold me softly, and gently caress my skin, touching my face so lightly, ive forgotten my every sin. but it doesn't matter near or far, i never doubt our love, for in my heart you always are, like the innocence of a dove. so although its valentines day, and right now i can't be with you, i have just a few words to say, three words that still feel new. happy valentines day, i love you.

title: Stewed Potato
author: d.
text: i love my life as a chunk of potato in the big vat of beef stew.  i spend my time swimming back and forth,  back and forth,  just waiting until the day i have the honor to be chosen to nourish another being.  i know that is my destiny.  i have to admit,  it is very trying physically to be heated almost to combustion and then watch my fellow vat-mates leave to face their destiny.  then alas,  i always seem to be left when they place me in the deep,  dark cave they call a refrigerator.  as i sit,  feeling the stew congile around my cooling,  stiffening self,  i ask myself how it could have happened that i,  once a part of divine potatoeness,  should be chosen for this profound journey of fate.       *inspired by mutant message down under*

title: Feelings
author: d.
text: feelings,  for him,  for me.  so confusing,  and yet strangely satisfying.  i don't know what to say or do.  if only he'd open up to me or i'd open up to him.  i don't think it's love,  only a mere teenage crush.  what do i even want? a hug,  a kiss,  maybe not.  maybe none of this is what i want.  is there a way to tell? or if he'd somehow tell me what he wants.  things could be better.  things could be worse.  it's nice to know there's always someone who cares.  how to sort it all out? what's the right thing to do? all these thoughts,  going round and round.  not quite a poem,  no rhyme at all,  but it's truths; it's emotion,  in a way.   ok,  so not really.

title: Snow is....
author: daniel
text: snow is the magic of which fun is made.  snow is the experience that doesn't come any ol' day.   snow is mysterious yet it makes itself known.  snow is for everyone no one person can own.   snow is soft,  gentle,  white,  and pure.  snow is sacred,  for loneliness snow will cure.   snow is the essence of a cold winter's day.  snow is what i dream of,  if i could have more then i would pay.   snow is priceless it can't be bought.  snow is a wonder who would have thought?  snow is a privilege that to come you must wait.  snow is so great that when it comes you can hardly think straight.   snow is the reason for hot chocolate and a fire nice and warm.  snow is a season where memories are born.   snow is special in its own little way.  snow is mortal and must leave,  for there is no way for it to stay.   snow is reliable and will come again another day.

title: A Tale of a slave/ A Play(2013)
author: danielle
text: you come to my country,  and tear up my home.   thinking to myself 'why wont this lazy people leave us alone. ' this is imposable,  these people are unstopable .   having no natural affection,  guidening others in the wrong drection .   stupidity i feel,  wishing this was not real.  greedy,  greedy are you not! killing my people with one shot.  the black man that tries,  of coares they do despise,  hatred in their hearts,  that feels like flying darts,  hurtful word soaring through the air like birds,  ones that all black people have heared,  do you hate me because the color of my skin? or the person deep with in? but you'll never know the person deep with in,  because your to busy holding up your chin! ''master,  master is it not,  please some water for me too for it is very hot!'' ' you think i would let you defaul my cup with those ugly lips?! shake it off and work those hips!' (laughter) no mercy did he show,  for this reason i am planning to go.  running with these feet of mine,  feeling like im running faster than time! looking behind,  at shock to what i find,  my masters behind me,  and he doesn't look so kind.  with a gun in his hand therefore i stop,  knowing if i go any father i would be killed with one shot! ' why do you run away you wicked slave,  did i not treat you good? or would you like it better in your grave?!' go ahead you should ! his friend called out.  no!!! i begged. (cowering) what he's backing down?!  quickly his friends smile turned into a frown.  he showed me mercy but his friend did not .  he snached the gun and shot me with one shot.  i was not dead but it was a little wound to the head,  lucky me,  i could pretend dead! as i lay there on the ground ,  i hear his car in a driving away sound.  free alast!!! for me atleast for now,  slavery had past! into a creeck i go,  to wash off this blood that was quickly dripping down to my nose.  although i have no food nor water or cash,  i sreamed in my head,  free at last!!!!!!

title: Swimming
author: danielle
text: i took my swim bag in my hand,   then smiled to let them know i was glad to be there.    we were all friends,  even the coach.  as i swam toward the wall,   the one whose touch meant i was finally done with the rest of the set,  i smiled to myself.    we were doing the â‘catch-up drillâ’  and pretending to â‘stab the fishâ’ at practice until our faces showed we were working hard,  bright with sweat.   i laughed and splashed my friends back,  then led them into the next set,   across the swimming pool and into another good day at swim team.  we stopped with relief,  seeing the knowing looks from gold,   which we all thought we would never make down the road.    i turned to my friend,  laughed like crazy,  and asked why and how he would ever say that.   water in my goggles,  a smile on my face,  and a lot of chlorine in my hair.    i put on a swim cap in the locker room,   and when i went out i again couldnâ’t help smiling when i saw my friends.   i took my fins from my friend,  then the front of the line from the other.    when i looked up,  the coachâ’s eyes met mine,   told me to do my flip turns,   knowing very well what it was all about.    outside,  a few cars already pulled up and kids hung around,   not eager to leave,  for the practice to end.    i put on my swimming suit that was so normal against the water of the pool.  that,  from some distance,  someone might have thought i was truly someone who belonged in a swimming pool with my friends.

title: A Grade 8 Graduation Poem
author: danielle
text: next year i hope to graduate,  this thought brings tears into my eye.  i hope to make it through grade eight,  and charish my friends until i die.   but as we walk the golden mile,  through each chapter of our life.  our willingness is worth our wile,  it guides us to and from our strife.   we'll have our ups-we'll have our downs,  but all in all we'll reach our goal.  no matter where life takes us now,  our aspirations fill our toll.   through our life we'll meet new friends,  we'll find a special some one two.  even though the road may end,  we'll keep our faith and make it through.   at times we'll feel like giving in,  we'll feel the road has got to rough.  but we'll find our soul within,  and make our way through times so tough.   so next year when i say goodbye,  i just may happen to hold that tear.  because i'll also say a ''hi'',  because the rest of my life starts here.

title: Finding Light Through Darkness
author: danielle
text: fading into darkness  seeing nothing but black  an endless waistland of nothing  no sound to be heard  nothing but the sound of my footsteps as i walk   the never ending darkness surrounds me  i think of all i love  as i search for the light of day   but that light stays hidden from me  hidden from my sight  just as the things i care about  flee from my gaze   this terrible darkness  fills me with dread and sorrow   when will i return?  to my life long past?   when will i see the light of day?  the ones i love?   when?   i ask this to the foreboding darknes  yet i get no answer  nothing but my own question  echoes back at me through the darkness   i am being consumed by darkness and sorrow  falling into a pool of fear   how will i escape this darkness?   how will i return?   this darkness overwhelms my senses  it rips at my heart  and tears at my soul  i am dying in this darkness   why must this be?   i cry tears of blood  it drips down my cheeks  and onto my clothes   it spills onto my lips  yet i feel no pain  how can i still be living?   i have no hope  my dreams have been shredded  the pieces float in endless darkness   reminding me of what i once was  what i once had   my clothes are soaked from the bloody tears  that have stained my cheeks   my heart is gone  ripped to pieces  my soul is dead and lost  torn by the malevoilent darkness   as i die i wonder  what is happening? why me?   the blood sinks to the floor  spilling into pools   i begin to see. . .   see the light of day   and the face of my love  fills my vision   he smiles as my eyes blink in the light  i am safe in his arms  where nothing can harm me   i am alive.

title: Are you afraid of the Dark?
author: danielle
text: there in the midst.  i see a huge figure.  it is coming towards me.  it is not making a sound.  i dont know what it is.  i dont know what to do.  the figure is large.  the figure is terrifying.  i run as fast as i can.  away from that thing.  it is coming.  i am terrifyed.  it is dark.  it is pitch black.  i wake up. it was just a dream.  it was the dark.  am i afraid? it was the fury in the figure that made me weep.  are you afraid?
